{"key":"post-9787001","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>9787001</id>\n<content>I keep dishes on an open shelf in my bedroom/lab. They get normal ambient room lighting during the day.&amp;nbsp; We live in a remote cabin in the mountains and have a wood burning stove for heat, so there's temp fluctuations.&amp;nbsp; To help make up for that and also to protect the dishes, they're placed into ziplock bags after sealing with parafilm.&amp;nbsp; I inflate the bags with sterile flow from my laminar flow hood, and then close them up.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>9787029</next>\n<prev>9786363</prev>\n<first>9785279</first>\n<last>9848467</last>\n<when>1234492316</when>\n<utime>02/13/09 04:31 AM</utime>\n</post>"}